&lt;/ol&gt;</content><author><name>Ovidiu Pârvu</name></author><category term="library" /><category term="technology" /><category term="reading" /><summary type="html">Storage aystems</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">How to set up a GitHub Pages technical blog?</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2020/05/25/how-to-set-up-github-pages-technical-blog" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to set up a GitHub Pages technical blog?" /><published>2020-05-25T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2020-05-25T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2020/05/25/how-to-set-up-github-pages-technical-blog</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2020/05/25/how-to-set-up-github-pages-technical-blog">&lt;p&gt;This post describes how to set up a GitHub Pages site for a technical blog like this one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Create a GitHub repository for hosting the blog source files: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ovidiuparvu/gh-pages-blog-template/generate&quot;&gt;gh-pages-blog-template&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Clone the GitHub repository created at step 1 into a local directory, which will be denoted as &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;BLOG_DIR&lt;/code&gt; for the remainder of this post.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Set up &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/documentation/installation/&quot;&gt;Ruby&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://bundler.io/&quot;&gt;Bundler&lt;/a&gt; locally.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Install the gems required for testing the blog locally by running in the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;BLOG_DIR&lt;/code&gt; directory the following:
    &lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt; bundle install
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Test the blog locally by running in the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;BLOG_DIR&lt;/code&gt; directory the command below and opening in a browser the URL printed when running the command:
    &lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt; bundle exec jekyll serve
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Customize the structure and contents of the blog to your own liking. If you are new to Jekyll, going through the &lt;a href=&quot;https://jekyllrb.com/docs/step-by-step/01-setup&quot;&gt;Step by Step Tutorial&lt;/a&gt; could help.
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Search for all occurrences of the string &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;YOUR_NAME&lt;/code&gt; in the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;BLOG_DIR&lt;/code&gt; directory and replace them (and the surrounding text) as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</content><author><name>Ovidiu Pârvu</name></author><category term="blog" /><category term="gh-pages" /><summary type="html">This post describes how to set up a GitHub Pages site for a technical blog like this one.</summary></entry></feed>